.TH "batadv_is_on_batman_iface" 9 "batadv_is_on_batman_iface" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
batadv_is_on_batman_iface \- check if a device is a batman iface descendant
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" batadv_is_on_batman_iface
.BI "(const struct net_device *net_dev "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "net_dev" 12
the device to check
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
If the user creates any virtual device on top of a batman-adv interface, it
is important to prevent this new interface from being used to create a new
mesh network (this behaviour would lead to a batman-over-batman
configuration). This function recursively checks all the fathers of the
device passed as argument looking for a batman-adv soft interface.
.SH "RETURN"
true if the device is descendant of a batman-adv mesh interface (or
if it is a batman-adv interface itself), false otherwise
